  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 00c9c9bb92b3b44fb84ca335c48467d8, type: 3}
  m_Name: Dialogue_Act1_CrookedPintle_BramKey
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Hollowfen.Dialogue.DialogueData
  _id: act1.crooked_pintle.bram.key
  _lines:
  - speaker: Wren
    text: Dad's letters grew shorter, then stopped. He wrote about the flooded fields,
      never how bad it was. I should have come sooner, Bram. Tell me what happened
      - and why you have the mill key.
    isCloseup: 1
    voiceClip: {fileID: 8300000, guid: e3339c81edf6b4517a4df1db97bf50f6, type: 3}
  - speaker: Bram
    text: Your father made every hardship sound like weather. The Wend changed course
      three winters ago and left the wheel over dry stones. When he took poorly,
      he brought me this key and asked me to keep the damp out until you came home.
      I did what I could. He was a good man, Wren, and a dear friend. I am sorry.
    isCloseup: 1
    voiceClip: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 9d756b19092dd4f3fa66e3d2f024af1e, type: 3}
  - speaker: Wren
    text: Thank you for keeping faith with him. I'll take the key now - and whatever
      waits at the mill. I've spent long enough being absent.
    isCloseup: 1
    voiceClip: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 67389332e582149f4a37aaa72afae9ef, type: 3}
